{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WNmS9Hhef9WMFjJX4a2fnC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t/**\n2\t * Model Resolution Module (Story 10-4).\n3\t *\n4\t * Resolves the effective model for a task dispatch using a 3-level cascade:\n5\t *   1. Task-level model (highest priority)\n6\t *   2. Agent-level model\n7\t *   3. Driver default model (lowest priority, must be valid)\n8\t *\n9\t * Architecture reference: Decision 4 in architecture-multi-framework.md.\n10\t */\n11\t\n12\t/**\n13\t * Resolves the effective model string using a task → agent → driver cascade.\n14\t *\n15\t * Empty strings, whitespace-only strings, `null`, and `undefined` are all\n16\t * treated as \"not set\" and fall through to the next level. Model strings are\n17\t * trimmed before use. The driver's `defaultModel` is the final fallback and\n18\t * must be a non-empty string — if it is falsy and no task/agent model is set,\n19\t * an error is thrown. If task or agent provides a valid model, the driver\n20\t * default is never validated (per architecture Decision 4 nullish-coalescing).\n21\t *\n22\t * @param task   - Object with an optional `model` field (e.g. workflow task)\n23\t * @param agent  - Object with an optional `model` field (e.g. resolved agent config)\n24\t * @param driver - Object with a required `defaultModel` field (e.g. AgentDriver)\n25\t * @returns The resolved model string\n26\t * @throws {Error} If `driver.defaultModel` is empty or falsy\n27\t */\n28\texport function resolveModel(\n29\t  task: { model?: string | null },\n30\t  agent: { model?: string | null },\n31\t  driver: { defaultModel: string },\n32\t): string {\n33\t  const taskModel = task.model?.trim() || undefined;\n34\t  const agentModel = agent.model?.trim() || undefined;\n35\t\n36\t  if (taskModel) {\n37\t    return taskModel;\n38\t  }\n39\t\n40\t  if (agentModel) {\n41\t    return agentModel;\n42\t  }\n43\t\n44\t  if (!driver.defaultModel?.trim()) {\n45\t    throw new Error(\n46\t      'Driver has no default model: driver.defaultModel must be a non-empty string',\n47\t    );\n48\t  }\n49\t\n50\t  return driver.defaultModel;\n51\t}\n52\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011ACjM7rS7kgs6kygtQ7sim","session_id":"f83470b7-c271-483e-ae93-7fe9bce4b683","uuid":"3d4dc339-3e91-464b-85db-dad1cfed5693","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:38:12.295Z"}
