{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0193UnVDBXkPXze8z91u3H4w","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]\n3\tlastStep: 8\n4\tstatus: 'complete'\n5\tcompletedAt: '2026-04-03'\n6\tinputDocuments:\n7\t  - prd.md (multi-framework orchestration PRD, 2026-04-03)\n8\t  - architecture.md (existing v1 architecture, brownfield context)\n9\t  - prd-validation-report.md (validation report, 4.5/5 Pass)\n10\tworkflowType: 'architecture'\n11\tproject_name: 'codeharness'\n12\tuser_name: 'BMad'\n13\tdate: '2026-04-03'\n14\t---\n15\t\n16\t# Architecture Decision Document\n17\t\n18\t_This document builds collaboratively through step-by-step discovery. Sections are appended as we work through each architectural decision together._\n19\t\n20\t## Project Context Analysis\n21\t\n22\t### Requirements Overview\n23\t\n24\t**Functional Requirements:**\n25\t38 FRs across 9 capability areas. The core is a driver abstraction layer (FR1-FR10) that normalizes 3 agent framework CLIs into a common `AgentDriver` interface with `StreamEvent` output. The workflow engine gains per-task `driver` and `model` fields (FR11-FR15). Cross-framework task execution uses explicit output contracts serialized as JSON (FR16-FR20). The Ink TUI gains a workflow graph component (FR24-FR30). Plugin ecosystem integration (gstack/omo) passes config to parent driver CLIs (FR21-FR23).\n26\t\n27\t**Non-Functional Requirements:**\n28\t18 NFRs across performance (driver spawn <3s, TUI update <500ms, health check <5s), integration (pinned CLI versions, backward-compatible schema, no plugin modifications), and reliability (crash detection <5s, atomic contract writes, idempotent re-runs). Single-user local CLI — no scalability or availability requirements.\n29\t\n30\t**Scale & Complexity:**\n31\t\n32\t- Primary domain: Node.js CLI extending existing Commander.js architecture\n33\t- Complexity level: Medium — one new architectural layer (drivers) on proven foundation\n34\t- Estimated architectural components: ~8 new (3 drivers, 1 driver factory, 1 output contract module, 1 TUI workflow component, workflow schema extension, model resolver)\n35\t\n36\t### Technical Constraints & Dependencies\n37\t\n38\t- **Existing architecture** — 10 decisions from v1 architecture remain valid: CLI↔Plugin boundary, state management, beads integration, template embedding, verification pipeline. This PRD extends, not replaces.\n39\t- **Agent SDK** — Claude Code Agent SDK (`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`) already in use for in-process dispatch. Stays as the claude-code driver implementation.\n40\t- **Codex CLI** — External binary (`codex`). Output format must be reverse-engineered from real CLI output. Auth via OpenAI API key or ChatGPT account.\n41\t- **OpenCode CLI** — External binary (`opencode`). Go-based. Output format must be reverse-engineered. Supports 75+ models with per-provider keys.\n42\t- **No programmatic SDK** — Neither Codex nor OpenCode expose a dispatch SDK. All integration is CLI wrapping via `child_process.spawn` with stdout/stderr parsing.\n43\t- **Ink/React TUI** — Existing TUI uses Ink 6 with React 19. New workflow graph component must fit the existing component architecture and 15 FPS render loop.\n44\t- **Workflow YAML schema** — Existing `workflow.schema.json` must be extended (not replaced) with `driver` and `model` fields. JSON Schema backward compatibility required.\n45\t\n46\t### Cross-Cutting Concerns Identified\n47\t\n48\t1. **Driver lifecycle management** — Spawning, monitoring, timeout, termination, crash recovery applies to all drivers. Must be uniform regardless of whether the driver is in-process (Agent SDK) or CLI-wrapped (Codex, OpenCode).\n49\t2. **Stream event normalization** — Every driver must produce `StreamEvent` objects. The TUI, cost tracker, and workflow engine all consume these. A driver that drops events or misparses output breaks everything downstream.\n50\t3. **Output contract integrity** — Cross-framework task execution depends on output contracts being complete, correctly serialized, and crash-safe. A corrupted contract means the next task gets garbage context.\n51\t4. **Model resolution cascade** — Task model → agent model → driver default must be consistent across workflow parsing, driver dispatch, and TUI display. A disagreement means the TUI shows one model while the driver uses another.\n52\t\n53\t## Starter Template Evaluation\n54\t\n55\t### Primary Technology Domain\n56\t\n57\tNode.js CLI tool — already built and running. TypeScript + tsup + Commander.js + Vitest. Ink 6 + React 19 for TUI. Published on npm as `codeharness`.\n58\t\n59\t### Starter Options Considered\n60\t\n61\t**N/A — Brownfield project.** The existing technology stack is established:\n62\t\n63\t- TypeScript strict mode, ESM modules\n64\t- tsup for build → `dist/`\n65\t- Commander.js for CLI parsing\n66\t- Vitest + c8 for testing/coverage\n67\t- BATS for bash integration tests\n68\t- Ink 6 + React 19 for terminal UI\n69\t- Claude Code Agent SDK for agent dispatch\n70\t\n71\t### Selected Starter: Existing codebase\n72\t\n73\t**Rationale:** No new project initialization needed. The multi-framework feature adds files to `src/lib/agents/drivers/`, extends `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`, and adds Ink components to `src/lib/ink-*.tsx`. All within the established architecture.\n74\t\n75\t**New modules to add:**\n76\t\n77\t```\n78\tsrc/lib/agents/drivers/\n79\t├── claude-code.ts      # Refactor existing dispatchAgent() into driver interface\n80\t├── codex.ts            # New — wraps codex CLI\n81\t├── opencode.ts         # New — wraps opencode CLI\n82\t├── factory.ts          # New — driver registry and resolution\n83\t└── types.ts            # Existing — extend AgentDriver interface\n84\t\n85\tsrc/lib/\n86\t├── model-resolver.ts   # New — task → agent → driver default cascade\n87\t├── output-contract.ts  # New — serialize/deserialize cross-framework contracts\n88\t└── ink-workflow.tsx     # New — TUI workflow graph component\n89\t```\n90\t\n91\t**Note:** No project initialization story needed. First story is driver interface formalization.\n92\t\n93\t## Core Architectural Decisions\n94\t\n95\t### Decision 1: Driver Interface Design\n96\t\n97\t**Decision:** Refactor `AgentDriver` interface to support both in-process (Agent SDK) and CLI-wrapped drivers uniformly. `dispatch()` returns `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>` instead of `spawn()` returning `AgentProcess`.\n98\t\n99\t**Interface:**\n100\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011ACjM7rS7kgs6kygtQ7sim","session_id":"f83470b7-c271-483e-ae93-7fe9bce4b683","uuid":"81ceeccd-3e65-441c-b679-452f730dd1fa","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:38:19.676Z"}
