{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JHBd2h21hZJ3ormyytEjgf","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here is the summary:\n\n---\n\n**Story 10-5: Workflow Engine Driver Integration** -- implemented and marked for review.\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Refactored `dispatchTaskWithResult()`** in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` to:\n   - Resolve driver via `getDriver(task.driver ?? 'claude-code')` from the factory\n   - Resolve model via `resolveModel(task, {model: definition.model}, driver)` 3-level cascade\n   - Build `DispatchOpts` with prompt, model, cwd, sourceAccess, plugins, timeout\n   - Call `driver.dispatch(opts)` and consume `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>`\n   - Extract output text, sessionId, cost from the result event\n   - Map error result events to `DispatchError` (RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK direct; AUTH/TIMEOUT to UNKNOWN)\n   - Removed `dispatchAgent` import; kept `DispatchError` import from `agent-dispatch.ts`\n\n2. **Updated all 95 existing tests** in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` to use driver mock pattern instead of `mockDispatchAgent`\n\n3. **Added 13 new driver-integration tests** covering: getDriver default, forward-compat driver field, DispatchOpts shape, resolveModel arguments, stream consumption, error mapping (RATE_LIMIT, AUTH->UNKNOWN), timeout pass-through, sourceAccess, no-dispatchAgent verification, loop block integration, retry prompt pass-through\n\n4. **Verification:** `npm run build` succeeds (zero TS errors), `npm run test:unit` passes 4321 tests across 164 files with zero regressions\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`\n- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`\n- `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-5-workflow-engine-driver-integration.md`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Workaround:** `task.max_budget_usd` is passed as `DispatchOpts.timeout` — the naming mismatch (budget vs timeout) is inherited from the story spec. Story 11-1 should clarify whether these are truly the same concept.\n- **Forward-compat casts:** Used `(task as { driver?: string }).driver` and `(task as { plugins?: readonly string[] }).plugins` since `ResolvedTask` doesn't have these fields yet (story 11-1). These casts are safe but ugly.\n- **ErrorCategory mapping:** AUTH and TIMEOUT from the driver's `ErrorCategory` map to UNKNOWN in `DispatchErrorCode` since that type doesn't include them. Story Dev Notes acknowledged this as acceptable for now.\n- **Cost field captured but unused:** The `cost` value from result events is extracted but not stored anywhere (the old `DispatchResult` shape didn't expose it either). Future stories may want to surface this.\n- **OOM during initial test run:** The first test run hit OOM before adding the factory/resolver mocks, because vitest tried to resolve the real `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` import chain. Adding the mocks fixed it. This is a pre-existing fragility in the test setup.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 42\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 14, Edit: 25, Grep: 10, Write: 0, Skill: 1, Glob: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): vitest run with OOM (~80 lines), vitest run with failures (~100 lines), npm test:unit full run (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 18 total reads (workflow-engine.test.ts read 5 times due to offset-based reading of large file)\n- Redundant operations: Multiple sequential reads of workflow-engine.test.ts could have been consolidated with larger offsets; some Grep calls for mockDispatchAgent patterns were exploratory before settling on replacement strategy"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a755270e4fc4fbb51 (use SendMessage with to: 'a755270e4fc4fbb51' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 128179\ntool_uses: 118\nduration_ms: 710048</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f83470b7-c271-483e-ae93-7fe9bce4b683","uuid":"fcff1131-8bfc-41d3-bc77-0