rser only returns `cost` and `sessionId` from result events, not error fields. This is OK for now since `ClaudeCodeDriver` yields `ResultEvent` objects directly (bypassing the parser), but CLI-wrapped drivers that parse NDJSON would lose error information. This is a future driver concern, not a regression.\n\n### LOW ISSUES (not fixed)\n\n6. **Double `dispatchTask` call in error mapping test** — The test at line ~2650 calls `dispatchTask` twice: once to check the throw message, once in a try/catch to check the error code. This is fragile and wastes cycles. Could be a single try/catch checking both properties.\n\n7. **`mockDispatchAgent` still hoisted and set up in `setupDefaultMocks`** — The old `dispatchAgent` mock is still present in test setup even though `dispatchAgent` is no longer imported by the engine. This is dead code in tests.\n\n### Tests Added\n\n- `maps SDK_INIT errorCategory to SDK_INIT DispatchErrorCode (halt-critical)`\n- `passes sessionId through DispatchOpts when resolved`\n- `does not include sessionId in DispatchOpts when not resolved`\n- `passes appendSystemPrompt through DispatchOpts with trace prompt`\n\n### Files Modified\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — restored sessionId/appendSystemPrompt threading, added SDK_INIT mapping\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — updated 2 existing tests, added 4 new tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/types.ts` — added `sessionId` and `appendSystemPrompt` to `DispatchOpts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts` — thread new opts through to SDK query\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-5-workflow-engine-driver-integration.md` — status to `verifying`, updated File List and Change Log\n\n### Verification\n\n- Build: zero TypeScript errors\n- Tests: 4325 passed across 164 files (4 new tests, 0 regres